#: ../../../release_details/9.4/vr-viewfrustum.md:1
msgid "Virtual/Mixed Reality rendering improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/vr-viewfrustum.md:3
msgid ""
"Changes to the view frustum calculation address proper rendering, "
"particularly by the hardware accelerated volume mapper "
"(`vtkGPUVolumeRayCastMapper`) when the head-mounted display (HMD) is "
"positioned inside the volume. The computation of the view frustum was "
"corrected by ensuring that the appropriate eye transform matrices are "
"accounted for when the VR camera is tracking the HMD."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/vr-viewfrustum.md:8
msgid "Deprecation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/vr-viewfrustum.md:10
msgid "The following APIs were deprecated:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/vr-viewfrustum.md:12
msgid "`vtkVRRenderWindow::SetTrackHMD()`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/vr-viewfrustum.md:13
msgid "`vtkVRRenderWindow::GetTrackHMD()`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/vr-viewfrustum.md:15
msgid ""
"Developers should instead rely on the new VR camera specific tracking flag:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/vr-viewfrustum.md:17
msgid "`vtkVRCamera::SetTrackHMD()`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/vr-viewfrustum.md:18
msgid "`vtkVRCamera::GetTrackHMD()`"
msgstr ""

